author: COMSOL
description: The stress-optical effect causes unwanted birefringence in a planar photonic waveguide. Plane strain analysis followed by an optical mode analysis show the resulting split of the fundamental modes. This example uses a generalized plane strain formulation taking the deformation in the z direction into account.
label: stress_optical_generalized.mph
